      "id": "GENUS_SITTA",
      "name": "Sitta",
      "rank": "GENUS",
      "description": "The only birds that routinely walk headfirst down tree trunks, gripping bark with powerful feet and using the bill to lever up bark and extract insects. They wedge nuts in bark crevices to hack them open — hence the name. The Eurasian Nuthatch plasters the entrance of its nest hole with mud to exactly its own body diameter.",
